p: TERRITORY OF WASHINGTON, County of Spokane } SS. Territory of Washington, Plaintiff vs. Sterling P. White, Defendant } In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Lincoln Judicial District thereof, holding terms at Cheney, Spokane County, in said Territory. To the Sheriff of Lincoln County, Greeting: IN THE NAME OF THE UNITED STATES, You are hereby commanded to summon F. M. Spencer and J.H. Hart to be and appear before the District Court afmean at the Court House, in Cheney, in said County, on the forthwith day of April A.D. 1885, at o'clock, M., to there give evi- dence in the above entitled cause on the part of said Defendant. Witness the Hon. George Turner Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the Seal there- of affixed, this 20 day of April A.D. 1885 Kate W. Frauerbach Clerk. By R. Dtrobach Deputy.
